cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is about the application of deep convolutional spiking neural networks (SNNs) to artificial intelligence (AI) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses learning rules, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, since the focus is on convolutional SNNs, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the energy efficiency of SNNs, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, since the paper is about AI tasks, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
